lead_paragraph: MURDER ON SAIPBOARD.--JAMES McGLUE 2d mate of the bark Lewis, Capt. WHITE, which arrived at Salem on Wednesday last, has been committed--having waived an examination-to answer the charge of murdering CHARLES A. JOHNSON, the chief mate, on the 1st of May last, while the bark was at anchor near the point of Zanzibar. The case is rather a mysterious one.
